value.0: Muscular and lean, this feline is obviously not just another pampered housecat. Several notches mar the edge of his left ear, and the tip of the right one is completely missing - though long healed over. Various other blemishes mark the cat's calico fur - from barely-seen jagged lines where deep scratches have become scars, to outright bald patches like the one at the base of his tail, and another under the right side of his chin. With all of these disfigurements, it might lead one to wonder if the cat was named for his multi-colored coat, or for his battlescars marring it.

Formerly the cellar boy and servant in the Keep, he has bulked up significantly as he has grown, yet still remains boyish.  Every now and then, his voice cracks while speaking, although that is becoming less and less frequent. His promotion to First Knight excites him, as well as his trip to the Kingdom of Kohlingen to receive training as a cavalryman.
